parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Faulty Grease Seals in Axle Assemblies
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the grease seals in the axle assemblies can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to a loss of braking power, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The brakes feel weak or spongy
the brake pads are contaminated with grease
the brake drums are coated with grease
the trailer is difficult to stop

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Lippert Axle Failure and Seal Leakage
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Lippert axle and seal leakage can cause the loss of braking ability, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Grease leakage through axle seals into the hub assembly

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A soft floor in the kitchen area of the RV can lead to structural damage, water intrusion, and potentially cause accidents or injuries due to tripping hazards.
symptoms: The floor in the kitchen area feels soft or spongy
the floor appears to be sagging or uneven
water damage or staining is visible on the floor or surrounding areas.
